wiki.categories_description: This feature enables the registration of categories for manual entries made by the organization. Categories are used for identifying the reasons for the entries.
wiki.search_filter_description: Apply specific filters to the register search.
wiki.organization_users_description: Here, you manage the users of your organization.
wiki.organization_categories_description: Here you manage the categories for manual entries of your organization.
wiki.search_user_by_name_description: Search for a specific register by name.
wiki.remove_filters_description: Remove applied filters and return the search to its initial state.
wiki.register_users_descriptions: Register new users to access your organization's dashboard and define their permissions.
wiki.generate_reports_descriptions: Generate reports of the founded registers based on the selected filters. The report can be downloaded on the page:
wiki.group_description: Access group and permissions to which the user is linked
wiki.description_description: Brief description to explain the purpose of the registration.
wiki.bank_maintain_description: This feature is used to perform maintenance on the banks that provide services to the Organization. It allows you to edit their information.
wiki.priority_description: Priority order for using that bank within the Organization's structure.
wiki.agency_description: Bank branch where the Organization holds an account with that bank.
wiki.account_description: Identification of the Organization's bank account with that bank.
wiki.bank_fee_description: The fee amount charged by the bank for processing the Organization's transactions.
wiki.cash_in_description: Identification of whether deposits are made to the Organization through that bank.
wiki.cash_out_description: Identification of whether withdrawals are made for the Organization through that bank.
wiki.general_configs_description: This feature is used to configure the general operational settings of an Organization. Types of receipts, limits, and technical settings are configured here.
wiki.cash_in_max_value_description: What is the maximum value that a deposit intermediated by the Organization can have.
wiki.cash_in_receive_by_pj_description: Allows deposits intermediated by the Organization to be made by Legal Entities (Pessoas Jur√≠dicas).
wiki.cash_in_max_value_receive_by_pj_descript: Defines the maximum value that a deposit made by a legal entity can have.
wiki.cash_in_receive_by_different_payer_descr: Allows deposits to be paid by individuals other than the buyer.
wiki.cash_in_max_value_receive_by_different_p: Defines a maximum value that a deposit paid by third parties can have.
wiki.cash_out_max_value_description: Defines the maximum value that a withdrawal intermediated by the Organization can have.
wiki.cash_in_max_value_by_month_description: Defines the monthly value limit that can be deposited per CPF (individual taxpayer identification number).
wiki.cash_out_max_value_by_month_description: Defines the monthly value limit that can be withdrawn per CPF.
wiki.cash_in_permission_description: Enables the intermediation of deposits by the Organization.
wiki.auto_switch_bank_acc_description: Enables the automatic switching of the executing bank for operations intermediated by the Organization. Currently, we have primary and secondary options, and based on characteristics such as maximum and minimum value limits in the accounts, these options are alternated to keep the operation active.
wiki.cash_out_permission_description: Enables the intermediation of withdrawals by the Organization.
wiki.check_last_waiting_pix_description: Enables the automatic status check of deposits that are in the 'waiting' status.
wiki.callback_deposit_api_enable_description: Enables the operation of deposit callbacks.
wiki.callback_withdraw_api_enable_description: Enables the operation of withdrawal callbacks.
wiki.cash_in_disabled_message_description: Informative message about whether deposits are enabled or not.
wiki.cash_out_disabled_message_description: Informative message about whether withdrawals are enabled or not.
wiki.time_to_prevent_repeated_withdraw_minute: Defines the interval in which a withdrawal with the same characteristics as another one already made can be repeated.
wiki.max_value_to_switch_bank_acc_description: Defines the maximum value that an Organization's account can reach before the automatic bank switching is performed.
wiki.min_value_to_switch_bank_acc_description: Defines the minimum value that an Organization's account can reach before the automatic bank switching is performed.
wiki.check_last_waiting_pix_time_minutes_desc: Defines how often (in minutes) the system will automatically check deposits in the 'waiting' status if automatic checking is enabled.
wiki.paybrokers_qr_code_expire_hours_descript: Defines how long (in hours) a QR code expires after its issuance if it is not paid.
wiki.time_receive_after_expire_qr_code_hours_: In some cases, QR code payments are made close to their expiration, which can lead to delayed validation by the financial institution, making it appear that the payment was not received. Therefore, this field allows you to define for how long after a QR code's expiration the receipt can still be validated with the financial institution. After this period, if no validation is received, the QR code is canceled.
wiki.totalizers_description: Through them, you can find some metrics related to the records below.
wiki.entity_total: Total number of entities registered in the system.
wiki.entity_inactive: Number of entities that have been inactivated.
wiki.aggregators_description: Here you manage the aggregators that use the dashboard.
wiki.aggregator_users_description: Here you manage the users who access your aggregator dashboard and define their permissions.
wiki.register_aggregator_users_descriptions: Register new users to access your dashboard and define their permissions.
wiki.aggregator_group_description: Group of permissions and accesses to which the user is linked.
wiki.aggregator_description: Aggregator to which the user is linked.
wiki.last_signin_date_description: Date of the user's last access to the system.
wiki.self_exclusion_description: Through this feature, a person can request self-inclusion in the blacklist for a period of time. This function prevents any operations from being performed with a specific CPF during that period.
wiki.register_self_exclusion_descriptions: Opens a modal to add a CPF to the blacklist and select the period of time during which the person will be restricted.
wiki.start_date_description: Initial date selected during the registration creation
wiki.end_date_description: End date selected during the registration creation
wiki.search_by_reason_description: Filter to search for blocks by reason
wiki.search_by_cpf_description: Filter to enter and search for a block by Individual's Registration (CPF)
wiki.reason_description: Reason that led to the block of that Individual's Registration (CPF)
wiki.create_user_name_description: Name of the user who blocked that Individual's Registration (CPF)
wiki.aggregator_blacklist_description: Here you manage the list of blockages by Individual's Registration (CPF).
wiki.partners_description: Here you manage the platforms that use the dashboard.
wiki.dashboard_description: Here you will find your main totals.
wiki.balance_description: The main balances available in your account.
wiki.balance_transaction: Available balance for transactions mediated by the organization.
wiki.balance_payment: Balance available for payments to suppliers mediated by the Organization.
wiki.balance_reserved: Reserved balance value, which does not contribute to the available balances used for operations. It is a balance consolidated by the Organization.
wiki.bank_total_description: Brings the total balance value of the Organization along with the IP. This value is the total balance of transactions carried out by the organization through the IP in question.
wiki.bank_blocked_value_description: Brings the value blocked for future operations of the Organization, which has been safeguarded by the IP.
wiki.bank_chart_description: Switches the view from Grid to a bar chart.
wiki.bank_card_description: Switches the view from Grid to bank cards.
wiki.last_sign_in_description: User's last access date to the system.
